Guix's Clang libc-search-path patch disables CUDA installation detection
entirely to avoid probing FHS locations such as /usr/local/cuda.  That also
breaks explicit CUDA roots passed with --cuda-path, which prevents Guix-built
CUDA packages from using Clang as a CUDA compiler.

Keep the rest of the Guix search-path patch intact, but allow Clang to honor an
explicit --cuda-path again.

diff --git a/clang/lib/Driver/ToolChains/Cuda.cpp b/clang/lib/Driver/ToolChains/Cuda.cpp
index 1078dba8f481..1462576ca870 100644
--- a/clang/lib/Driver/ToolChains/Cuda.cpp
+++ b/clang/lib/Driver/ToolChains/Cuda.cpp
@@ -132,9 +132,6 @@ CudaInstallationDetector::CudaInstallationDetector(
     const Driver &D, const llvm::Triple &HostTriple,
     const llvm::opt::ArgList &Args)
     : D(D) {
-  // Don't look for CUDA in /usr.
-  return;
-
   struct Candidate {
     std::string Path;
     bool StrictChecking;
